Text.val: 17.09.2012 SH SCR17538 Changed Unicode fields back to alpha where SQL is used

ExpSyntax.val: 'CREATE TABLE QTEMP/MGSTSJ (JOB CHAR (132 ) NOT NULL WITH DEFAULT)'

SQL_STMT_U.val: SELECT SUBSTR(JOB , 45 , 6) FROM qtemp/MGSTSJ WHERE SUBSTR(JOB , 2, 5) = 'Jobs ' or SUBSTR(JOB , 2, 5) = 'Taken' FOR READ ONLY WITH NC OPTIMIZE FOR 100 ROWS
SELECT SUBSTR(JOB , 45 , 5) FROM qtemp/MGSTSJ WHERE SUBSTR(JOB , 2, 5) = '% CPU' FOR READ ONLY WITH NC OPTIMIZE FOR 100 ROWS

ExpSyntax.val: 'CPYSPLF FILE(QPDSPSTS) TOFILE(QTEMP/MGSTSJ) JOB(*) SPLNBR(*LAST) TOMBR(*FIRST) MBROPT(*REPLACE) '

SQL_STMT_U.val: SELECT SUBSTR(JOB , 111 , 8) FROM qtemp/MGSTSJ WHERE SUBSTR(JOB , 72, 5) = 'ruikt' or SUBSTR(JOB , 72, 5) = 'ystem' FOR READ ONLY WITH NC OPTIMIZE FOR 100 ROWS
